# Technical Project Summary: PropShield System Deep Dive

This document provides a comprehensive A-Z technical breakdown of the PropShield Property Insurance System, structured for a 15-slide presentation.

---

## Slide 1: Title Slide
**Title:** PropShield: Technical Architecture & API Full-Stack Overview
**Subtitle:** A deep dive into Entities, Controllers, and Endpoints
* **Presenter:** [Your Name]
* **Focus:** Full-cycle insurance management from registration to claim payout.

---

## Slide 2: System Architecture Overview
**Built with Modern Enterprise Standards:**
* **Layers:** 
    * **Domain:** Core entities, enums, and base logic (Independent).
    * **Application:** Services, Interfaces, and DTOs (Business Logic).
    * **Infrastructure:** EF Core Persistence, Repositories, Migrations.
    * **API:** RESTful endpoints with ASP.NET Core 8.0.
* **Frontend:** Angular Standalone components with Tailwind CSS integration.

---

## Slide 3: Core Domain Entities (1/3)
**User & Identity:**
* **ApplicationUser:** Extends identity with `FullName`, `Role` (Admin, Agent, Customer, ClaimsOfficer), `WalletBalance`, and `IsActive`.
* **RefreshToken:** Manages long-lived session security.
* **BaseEntity:** Common properties like [Id](file:///e:/Capstone/PropertyInsuranceSystem/API/Controllers/PolicyRequestsController.cs#20-25), `CreatedAt`, and `UpdatedAt`.

---

## Slide 4: Core Domain Entities (2/3)
**Product & Policy:**
* **PropertyCategory & SubCategory:** Defines property types (e.g., Residential -> Apartment).
* **PropertyPlans:** Insurance products with `BaseCoverageAmount`, `CoverageRate`, `BasePremium`, and `AgentCommission`.
* **PolicyRequest:** The lifecycle container for a customer's insurance journey.

---

## Slide 5: Core Domain Entities (3/3)
**Claims & Finance:**
* **Claim:** Detailed record of loss with `IncidentDate`, `IncidentType`, `ClaimAmount`, `PhotoUrls`, and `Status`.
* **Invoice:** Financial record generated upon policy purchase or claim approval.
* **Notification:** Real-time user alerts for status changes.

---

## Slide 6: AuthController (Identity Management)
**Endpoints (A-Z):**
* `POST /api/Auth/register`: Self-registration for Customers.
* `POST /api/Auth/login`: Secure login returning JWT and user roles.
* `POST /api/Auth/create-user` [Admin]: Management tool to create Agents or Claims Officers.
* `POST /api/Auth/redeem`: System for processing wallet withdrawals/payouts.

---

## Slide 7: PropertyPlans & Category Controllers
**Product Management:**
* `GET /api/PropertyPlans`: Fetches all available insurance plans (filtered by category).
* `POST /api/PropertyPlans` [Admin]: Create new insurance products with custom rates.
* `DELETE /api/PropertyPlans/{id}`: Remove outdated plans.
* `GET /api/Category`: Retrieve hierarchy of property types.

---

## Slide 8: PolicyRequestsController (Customer Workflow)
**The Insurance Journey - Initiation:**
* `POST /api/PolicyRequests/create`: Customer submits basic request.
* `GET /api/PolicyRequests/customer/my-requests`: Personal dashboard.
* `PUT /api/PolicyRequests/{id}/submit-form`: Customer provides specific property details (Age, Value, Photos).
* `PUT /api/PolicyRequests/{id}/buy`: Final customer confirmation of the calculated premium.

---

## Slide 9: PolicyRequestsController (Admin & Agent)
**The Insurance Journey - Processing:**
* `GET /api/PolicyRequests/admin/pending`: Global queue of new requests.
* `PUT /api/PolicyRequests/{id}/assign-agent/{agentId}`: Manual dispatching to agents.
* `GET /api/PolicyRequests/agent/assigned`: Agent's personal work queue.
* `PUT /api/PolicyRequests/{id}/send-form`: Agent pushes specialized forms to customers.

---

## Slide 10: PolicyRequestsController (Risk & Finalization)
**Closing the Loop:**
* `PUT /api/PolicyRequests/{id}/calculate-risk` [Agent]: Algorithmic determination of premium based on property age and value.
* `PUT /api/PolicyRequests/{id}/admin-approve`: Final gatekeeper approval before the policy becomes active.
* `GET /api/PolicyRequests/admin/all`: Complete history audit.

---

## Slide 11: ClaimsController (The Safety Net)
**Handling Losses:**
* `POST /api/Claims` [Customer]: File a new claim via multipart/form-data (includes metadata + photos).
* `GET /api/Claims/pending` [ClaimsOfficer]: queue of claims needing review.
* `PUT /api/Claims/{id}/verify` [ClaimsOfficer]: Decision endpoint (Approve/Reject) with logic for invoice triggering.
* `GET /api/Claims/history`: Full archive of past claim decisions.

---

## Slide 12: AdminController & Statistics
**System Oversight:**
* `GET /api/Admin/stats`: High-level metrics for dashboard graphs.
    * Total Customers, Agents, and Policies.
    * Revenue Growth tracking.
    * Performance leaderboard (Top Plans & Top Agents).
* `GET /api/Admin/agents`: User management for active agents.

---

## Slide 13: Invoices & Notifications
**Communication & Finance:**
* `GET /api/Invoices`: Historical record of all premium payments and claim payouts.
* `GET /api/Notifications`: Individual user alert inbox.
* **Logic:** Notifications are auto-triggered by the [ClaimsService](file:///e:/Capstone/PropertyInsuranceSystem/Application/Services/ClaimsService.cs#10-154) and `PolicyRequestService`.

---

## Slide 14: DTO & Data Transfer Layer
**Clean Data Boundaries:**
* **Request DTOs:** [CreateClaimDto](file:///e:/Capstone/PropertyInsuranceSystem/Application/DTOs/CreateClaimDto.cs#3-18), `LoginRequestDto`, `SubmitPropertyDto`.
* **Response DTOs:** `PlanResponseDto`, `AdminStatsDto`, `AuthResponseDto`.
* **Purpose:** Ensures internal entities are never exposed directly, maintaining security and flexibility.

---

## Slide 15: Security & Technical Safeguards
**Robustness at Core:**
* **JWT Authentication:** Secure stateless communication across all layers.
* **Role-Based Access Control (RBAC):** Strict attribute-based protection on every controller endpoint.
* **File Upload Security:** GUID-based renaming and controlled wroot directory management.
* **EF Core Migrations:** Versioned database schema management.
